      ],
      "content": "Crumbling stone steps ascend through a broken arch. The dome above is shattered — great rents in the copper skin let starlight pour through in silver columns. Dust motes drift in the beams like slow constellations.\n\nThe air smells of old stone and cold metal. Something glints on a pedestal near the entrance."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
