        ]
      ],
      "content": "A grand rotunda opens beneath what remains of the dome. The floor is inlaid with a vast star chart — constellations traced in tarnished silver wire across dark stone. Three corridors branch from the central space: west into shadow, east into a faint golden glow, and a spiral stair climbs upward through the ceiling.\n\nA set of stairs descends into darkness at the centre of the chart."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "cartographers-instrument:place:west-wing"
        ],
        [
          "t",
