        ]
      ],
      "content": "The highest point of the observatory. The dome is entirely gone here — nothing between you and the sky. A great telescope points upward, its brass barrel green with verdigris. The view is staggering: stars beyond counting, the Milky Way a river of light.\n\nBeneath the telescope, a crystalline structure sits on a marble plinth — faceted like a diamond, cold to the touch."
    },
