          "ambient",
          "0.7"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "You descend into a chamber that should not exist — a perfect sphere hollowed from the bedrock beneath the observatory. The walls are polished to a mirror finish, and in them you see not your reflection but *stars*. The entire night sky, projected from some impossible source, turning slowly around you.\n\nThe three notes you awakened — the root, the third, the fifth — converge here. The chord resolves. The composition is complete.\n\nThe cartographer's work is finished. The music of the spheres plays on."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
