          "visited",
          ""
        ]
      ],
      "content": "**The Music of the Spheres**\n\nThe chord resolves — root, third, fifth — and the Star Chamber sings. The mirrors on the walls show not reflections but the sky itself, turning slowly, endlessly, each star a note in an infinite score.\n\nYou understand now what the cartographer spent a lifetime charting. Not the positions of the stars, but their *sound*. The universe is a composition, and you have played its opening chord.\n\nThe instrument grows warm in your hands. The crystal at its centre pulses once, twice — then settles into a steady glow, beating in time with something vast and distant.\n\nThe cartographer's ghost appears beside you. For the first time, it smiles.\n\n*Thank you. The composition is complete. The spheres will sing it forever now.*\n\nThe figure fades. The music plays on.\n\n---\n\n*You completed The Cartographer's Instrument.*"
